Header: Addresses Balance §3 #1 (vertical pull under-trained — weighted pull-ups today) and §3 #3 (conditioning monoculture — row intervals, no bike/KB). Squat day per assumption §4 (bias loads up).

Intensity: 7.5/10
Duration: ~55 mins

Warm-up: 10 mins
- 5 min easy row or bike to break a sweat
- Squat ramp: empty bar x 8, 135 x 5, 185 x 3, 225 x 2, 275 x 1 (then start working sets)
- Band pull-aparts 2x15 to prime upper back

Section 1 — Back Squat
Every 3:00 for 5 sets
Back squat 5 reps @ 305#

Notes: +10# from your 4/21 5x5 (295# clean). 305# = 81% of 1RM, the productive zone for 5x5 hypertrophy. Do NOT ride this to 315# even if it feels light — that's a planned test-day load, not a Tuesday squat. Brace, sit between hips, drive heels.

Section 2 — Vertical Pull + Rear Delt (superset, every 2:30 for 4 sets)
- Weighted pull-up 5 reps @ 35#
- Face pulls 12 reps with rope/band (light, ~20-25# on cable)

Notes: This is the priority accessory of the week. You haven't trained vertical pull since 4/22 and it's running 0.6:1 against vertical push. If 35# x 5 moves clean across all 4 sets, next pull-up day try 40#. Face pulls: high elbows, pull rope to forehead, pause 1s — this is your zero-history rear-delt fix. Do not skip.

Section 3 — Row Conditioning
5 rounds for time
- 250m row sprint
- Rest 90 seconds between rounds

Notes: Target sub-1:00 each 250m. New conditioning modality (rower hasn't appeared in 28 days — only bike + carry AMRAP). Push 90%+ each interval, full recovery between.

Section 4 — Anti-rotation core (not for time, 3 sets)
- Pallof press 10 reps each side (medium band or cable)
- Hollow body hold 30s

Notes: Pallof is anti-rotation — different stimulus than your usual Copenhagen plank. Quiet hips, resist the cable pulling you to the side. No momentum.

# What to log
Just write what you did under workout/20260427 — load, sets, reps, and any failures or RPE if a set felt notable. If you skip a section, note why so I can adjust next week.
